<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="17Dec1917"><font color="red">PM 17 December 1917</font>, <cite>Letters I</cite> (JJ to Claud Sykes): In the hurry of catching post yesterday I forgot to make following changes: (1) in description of the boy Sargent for &lsquo;wheywhite&rsquo; read &lsquo;wheysour&rsquo; (2) After Mr Deasy&apos;s words  &lsquo;<i>I paid my way</i>&rsquo; for  &lsquo;Quite right. Quite right&rsquo; read  &lsquo;Good man. Good man&rsquo;. (3) In Mr Deasy&apos;s speech which begins,  &lsquo;Mark my words,&rsquo; omit the sentence,  &lsquo;And now it has come.&rsquo; Snowing here. Hope you got MS all right. Am at work now on last part of Telemachia.</div>
